cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.SE, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses legal implications and emerging threats associated with using cloud technologies for a video surveillance management system, indicating a focus on security and privacy concerns. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper explores the opportunity for distributed computing techniques of cloud storage to support a high-resolution video surveillance management system, indicating a focus on distributed computing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses the requirements for a high-resolution video surveillance management system, indicating a focus on computer vision and image processing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses various Software as a Service (SaaS), Platform as a Service (PaaS), and Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) cloud computing providers and their capabilities, indicating a focus on software engineering. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the network bandwidth requirements for a high-resolution video surveillance management system and explores the use of cloud technologies to support it, indicating a focus on networking and internet architecture.
